Document: StreamPeerBuffer
Path: godot/classes/class_streampeerbuffer.rst
Summary: A data buffer stream peer using a byte array for handling binary data in network sessions.

A StreamPeerBuffer object keeps an internal cursor which is the offset in bytes to the start of the buffer. Get and put operations are performed at the cursor position and will move the cursor accordingly. To handle binary data stored in files, FileAccess can be used directly. This object can be used to handle binary data from network sessions.
