Document: StreamPeerBuffer  
Path: godot/classes/class_streampeerbuffer.rst  
Summary: Methods for managing data buffer operations including clearing, duplicating, resizing, and cursor control.  

Method: clear() → void. Clears the data_array and resets the cursor.  
Method: duplicate() → StreamPeerBuffer. Returns a new StreamPeerBuffer with the same data_array content.  
Method: get_position() → int. Returns the current cursor position.  
Method: get_size() → int. Returns the size of data_array.  
Method: resize(size: int) → void. Resizes the data_array. This doesn't update the cursor.  
Method: seek(position: int) → void. Moves the cursor to the specified position. Position must be a valid index of data_array.